description: The four connected cavities (hollow spaces) centrally located within the brain that connect posteriorly with the central canal of the spinal cord.
label: Brain Ventricle

description: A centrally placed component of the ventricular system of the brain located in the diencephalon. Cerebrospinal fluid from the lateral ventricles flows into the third ventricle via the foramina of Monroe and exits the third ventricle via the aqueduct of Sylvius. The thalamus and hypothalamus border the lateral walls of the third ventricle.
label: Third Ventricle

description: A diamond-shaped cavity filled with cerebrospinal fluid within the pons extending between the obex in the caudal medulla and the aqueduct of Sylvius in the cerebellum.
label: Fourth Ventricle

description: The rostral extensions of the ventricular system of the brain consisting of two cavities, one on each side of the brain within the central regions of each cerebral hemisphere.  Cerebrospinal fluid flows from the lateral ventricles into the centrally third ventricle via the foramen of Monroe.
label: Lateral Ventricle

description: A white matter structure within the cleft that separates the left and right cerebral hemispheres in the mammalian brain. It is composed of a wide, flat bundle of 200-250 million axonal projections.
label: Corpus Callosum

description: The portion of the brain located at the base of the skull that is responsible for balance, equilibrium and movement.
label: Cerebellum

description: The part of the brain located anterior to the parietal lobes at the front of each cerebral hemisphere.
label: Frontal Lobe

description: One of the lobes of the cerebral hemisphere located superiorly to the occipital lobe and posteriorly to the frontal lobe. Cognition and visuospatial processing are its main functions.
label: Parietal Lobe

description: One of the cerebral lobes. It is located inferior to the frontal and parietal lobes and anterior to the occipital lobe.
label: Temporal Lobe

description: Clusters of neurons comprising the globus pallidus, putamen, caudate, nucleus accumbens, substantia nigra and subthalamic nucleus. They are involved with high level aspects of inhibitory motor activity in coordination with the excitation commands issued from the cerebellum.
label: Basal Ganglia

description: An ovoid mass composed predominantly of gray substance and associated laminae of white substance. The thalamus is divided into anterior, medial, and lateral parts. The function of the thalamus is to relay sensory impulses and cerebellar and basal ganglia projections to the cerebral cortex. The thalamus is positioned within the posterior part of the diencephalon forming most of each lateral wall of the third ventricle.
label: Thalamus

description: Three sections, the midbrain, pons and medulla oblongata, that are located at the base of the brain. The brain stem regulates the central nervous system, and is vital as a conduit for motor and sensory innervations.
label: Brain Stem

description: The dorsal part or roof plate of the midbrain, which consists of the pretectal area and the paired superior and inferior colliculi.
label: Tectum Mesencephali

description: The middle portion of the brainstem located between the midbrain and the medulla oblongata. The fourth ventricle lies dorsal to the pons which also contains the motor trigeminal nuclei and the abducens nuclei. The cerebellum contributes a large number of afferent fibers to the pons.
label: Pons Varolii

description: One of the four regions of cortex in each cerebral hemisphere. It is located posterior to the temporal lobe and inferior to the parietal lobe.
label: Occipital Lobe

description: The lower portion of the brainstem located between the pons and brainstem. This structure contains several descending and ascending tracts, lower cranial nerve nuclei, a significant proportion of the reticular system of the brainstem and other structures.
label: Medulla Oblongata

description: An important supervisory center in the brain, rich in ganglia, nerve fibers, and synaptic connections. It is composed of several sections called nuclei, each of which controls a specific function. The hypothalamus regulates body temperature, blood pressure, heartbeat, metabolism of fats and carbohydrates, and sugar levels in the blood. Through direct attachment to the pituitary gland, the hypothalamus also meters secretions controlling water balance and milk production in the female. The role of the hypothalamus in awareness of pleasure and pain is well established in the laboratory. It is involved in the expression of emotions, such as fear and rage, and in sexual behaviors. Despite its numerous vital functions, the hypothalamus in humans accounts for only 1/300 of total brain weight, and is about the size of an almond. Structurally, it is joined to the thalamus; the two work together to monitor the sleep-wake cycle.
label: Hypothalamus

description: A region of the brain at the junction of the pons, cerebellum, and medulla. It is a frequent site of tumor formation.
label: Cerebellopontine Angle

description: A curved gray matter structure of the temporal lobe lying on the floor of the lateral ventricle of the brain.
label: Hippocampus

description: The outer layer of the cerebrum composed of neurons and unmyelinated nerve fibers. It is responsible for memory, attention, consciousness and other higher levels of mental function.
label: Cerebral Cortex

description: A region in the brain that is located below the tentorium cerebelli and contains the cerebellum.
label: Infratentorial Brain

description: An invaginated portion of the cerebral cortex forming the base of the sylvian fissure.  It is part of the lateral side of the cortex and its function includes the processing of emotions, memory, and higher autonomic control.
label: Central Lobe

description: An anatomic structure formed by the crossing of the two optic nerves under the hypothalamus.
label: Optic Chiasm

description: The portion of the spinal cord located in the cervical region.
label: Cervical Spinal Cord

description: The portion of the spinal cord located in the thoracic region.
label: Thoracic Spinal Cord

description: The outermost, toughest, and most fibrous of the three membranes (meninges) that surround and protect the brain and spinal cord.
label: Dura Mater

description: Evidence of spinal cord dura mater.
label: Spinal Cord Dura Mater

description: Any one of three membranes that surround the brain and spinal cord.
label: Meninges

description: An organ composed of grey and white matter containing billions of neurons that is the center for intelligence and reasoning. It is protected by the bony cranium.
label: Brain

description: A set of neural connections within the central nervous system, beginning with the retina and terminating in the occipital cortex, that provides the ability to process visual images.
label: Visual Pathway

description: The second cranial nerve.
label: Optic Nerve

description: The part of the nervous system that consists of the brain, spinal cord, and meninges.
label: Central Nervous System

description: One of the contractile organs of the body.
label: Muscle

description: Muscles of the lower back whose actions involve the flexion of the hips and lumbar spine. The term may refer to psoas major muscle and psoas minor muscle, both located in the lower back.
label: Psoas Muscle

description: A muscle located in the anterior aspect of the abdominal wall.
label: Anterior Abdominal Wall Muscle

description: Any of the skeletal muscles that form the buttocks. These muscles are responsible for hip abduction and extension as well as movement of the thigh.
label: Gluteal Muscle

description: One of the three gluteal muscles on the lateral surface of the pelvic bone that abducts and rotates the thigh located on the left side of the body.
label: Left Gluteus Medius

description: A fan-shaped muscle of mastication that originates from and fills the temporal fossa, and inserts on the coronoid process of the mandible; it functions to elevate and retract the mandible.
label: Temporal Muscle

description: Fibromuscular tissue that separates the thoracic from the abdominal cavity. It increases the volume of the thoracic cavity through contractions, thus facilitating respiration.
label: Diaphragm

description: Two cup shaped areas, one each on the lateral side of the lower pelvis that house the head of the femur to form the ball and socket joint of the hip.
label: Acetabulum

description: A type of hinge joint located between the forearm and upper arm.
label: Elbow Joint

description: A gliding joint between the distal ends of the tibia and fibula and the proximal end of the talus.
label: Ankle Joint

description: A joint connecting the lower part of the femur with the upper part of the tibia. The lower part of the femur and the upper part of the tibia are attached to each other by ligaments. Other structures of the knee joint include the upper part of the fibula, located below and parallel to the tibia, and the patella which moves as the knee bends.
label: Knee Joint

description: The structural organ comprised of specialized connective tissue that forms the skeletal components of the body.
label: Bone

description: Any of thirty-three ring-shaped structures that form the vertebral column which surrounds and protects the spinal cord. Each vertebra consists of a bony body with its superior and inferior articular surfaces covered by hyaline cartilage. The body includes the centrum anteriorly and vertebral arch posteriorly. The articular surfaces of the vertebrae are connected by a fibrocartilaginous intervertebral disc.
label: Vertebra

description: The fourth of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C4 Vertebra

description: The seventh of the seven cervical vertebrae.
label: C7 Vertebra

description: The first thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T1 Vertebra

description: The third thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T3 Vertebra

description: The fourth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T4 Vertebra

description: The eleventh thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T11 Vertebra

description: The tenth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T10 Vertebra

description: The second thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T2 Vertebra

description: The fifth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T5 Vertebra

description: The sixth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T6 Vertebra

description: The eighth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T8 Vertebra

description: The ninth thoracic vertebra counting from the top down.
label: T9 Vertebra

description: The second lumbar vertebra counting from the top down.
label: L2 Vertebra

description: The sixth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down.
label: Rib 6

description: The seventh rib counting from the top of the rib cage down.
label: Rib 7

description: The ninth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down.
label: Rib 9

description: The flat triangle-shaped bone that connects the humerus with the clavicle in the back of the shoulder.
label: Scapula

description: The long, flat bone connecting with the cartilages of the first seven ribs and the clavicle.
label: Sternum

description: A light and spongy bone that is cubical in shape. This bone is positioned at the anterior part of the cranium, sitting between the two orbits, at the roof of the nose. It consists of four parts: a horizontal or cribriform plate; a perpendicular plate; and two lateral masses or labyrinths.
label: Ethmoid Bone

description: The lower jaw bone holding the lower teeth.
label: Mandible

description: The upper jawbone in vertebrates; it is fused to the cranium.
label: Maxilla

description: The triangular bone, made up of 5 fused bones of the spine, located in the lower area of the spine between the fifth lumbar vertebra and the coccyx.
label: Sacrum

description: The upper leg bone positioned between the pelvis and the knee.
label: Femur

description: The upper arm bone between the shoulder and elbow.
label: Humerus

description: The broad, dorsal, upper, and widest of the three principal bones composing either half of the pelvis.
label: Ilium

description: Either of the two bones (left and right) that form the front of the pelvis.
label: Pubic Bone

description: The thin wall between the two nasal cavities.
label: Nasal Septum

description: The vertebrae of the thoracic spine, numbered one through twelve in man.
label: Thoracic Spine

description: Those vertebrae between the ribs and the pelvis, L1-L5 in man.
label: Lumbar Spine

description: The short, constricted portion of the thigh bone between the femur head and the trochanter.
label: Femoral Neck

description: The highest portion of the femoral bone that articulates with the acetabulum.
label: Head of the Femur

description: A series of bones, muscles, tendons, and other tissues reaching from the base of the skull to the tailbone. The vertebral column forms the axis of the skeleton and encloses as well as protects the spinal cord and the fluid surrounding the spinal cord.
label: Vertebral Column

description: The bones that form the head, made up of the bones of the braincase and face.
label: Skull

description: The portion of the skull that forms the floor on which the brain lies. The internal surface of the cranial base has three large depressions that lie on different levels known as the anterior, middle, and posterior cranial fossae.
label: Base of the Skull

description: Space between the dura mater and the walls of the vertebral canal.
label: Epidural Spinal Canal Space

description: The anterior portion of the head extending from the forehead to the chin and ear to ear. The facial structures contain the eyes, nose and mouth, cheeks and jaws.
label: Face

description: The fallopian tube that extends from the uterus to the ovary in the right side of the pelvic cavity.
label: Right Fallopian Tube

description: One of the paired female reproductive glands containing the ova or germ cells; the ovary's stroma is a vascular connective tissue containing numbers of ovarian follicles enclosing the ova.
label: Ovary

description: The part of the endometrium that is located in the anterior uterine wall.
label: Anterior Endometrium

description: The lower part of the uterus occupying the region between the isthmus of the uterus and the vagina. It is divided into supravaginal and vaginal portions.
label: Cervix Uteri

description: The part of the endometrium that is located in the posterior uterine wall.
label: Posterior Endometrium

description: The upper, smaller part of the prostate between the ejaculatory ducts and the urethra.
label: Middle Lobe of the Prostate

description: The lowest part of the prostate gland adjacent to the superior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm.
label: Apex of the Prostate

description: The uppermost part of the prostate gland adjacent to the bladder wall.
label: Base of the Prostate

description: The most distal portion of the penis covered by the foreskin.
label: Glans Penis

description: The area between the lungs; it contains the thymus, some lymph nodes, and vessels and branches of the internal thoracic artery.
label: Anterior Mediastinum

description: The part of the lower portion of the mediastinum that is located behind the pericardium.
label: Posterior Mediastinum

description: The part of the pancreas from the point where it crosses the portal vein to the point where it enters the lienorenal ligament.
label: Body of the Pancreas

description: The left extremity of the pancreas within the lienorenal ligament.
label: Tail of the Pancreas

description: That portion of the pancreas lying in the concavity of the duodenum.
label: Head of the Pancreas

description: A portion of the pancreas that extends behind the superior mesenteric artery and superior mesenteric vein.
label: Uncinate Process of Pancreas

description: The smaller lobe of the liver extending into the left side of the body.
label: Left Lobe of the Liver

description: The larger lobe of the liver extending into the right side of the body.
label: Right Lobe of the Liver

description: The initial part of the pyloric canal of the stomach. This site contains endocrine cells that produce gastrin and somatostatin.
label: Antrum Pylori

description: Small tissue projection existing as a cecal diverticulum with a questionable history of vestigial versus specialized organ.
label: Appendix

description: The first part of the colon (large intestine) that starts in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen and ends at the transverse colon in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen.
label: Ascending Colon

description: The bend of the colon at the juncture of its ascending and transverse portions.
label: Hepatic Flexure

description: The third division of the colon (large intestine). It communicates with the ascending colon in the upper right-hand quadrant of the abdomen and the descending colon in the upper left-hand quadrant.
label: Transverse Colon

description: The main section of the digestive tube that connects the esophagus to the small intestine. The body proper excludes the upper and lower sections of the fundus and pyloric portion respectively.
label: Body of Stomach

description: A blind pouch-like commencement of the colon in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen at the end of the small intestine and the start of the large intestine.
label: Cecum

description: The area around the esophagogastric mucosal junction where the esophageal mucosa transitions into the gastric mucosa.
label: Gastric Cardia

description: The part of the large intestine measured from the cecum to the rectum consisting of ascending, transverse, descending and sigmoid portions. The purpose of the colon is to remove water from digested food prior to excretion.
label: Colon

description: The fourth portion of the large intestine (colon) that communicates with the transverse colon in the left-upper quadrant of the abdomen and the rectum below.
label: Descending Colon

description: The terminal portion of the gastrointestinal tract, extending from the rectosigmoid junction to the anal canal.
label: Rectum

description: The portion of the stomach that lies above the cardiac notch. It allows for the accumulation of gases produced by chemical digestion.
label: Fundus of the Stomach

description: The anatomical location where the esophagus joins to the stomach.
label: Gastroesophageal Junction

description: The lateral and inferior border of the stomach. Attached to it is the greater omentum.
label: Greater Curvature of the Stomach

description: The section of the intestines between the pylorus and cecum. The small intestine is approximately 20 feet long and consists of the duodenum, the jejunum, and the ileum. Its main function is to absorb nutrients from food as the food is transported to the large intestine.
label: Small Intestine

description: The portion of the large intestine that includes the descending and sigmoid colon.
label: Left Colon

description: The right border of the stomach.  It is concave in shape and extends from the cardiac orifice to the pyloric orifice.
label: Lesser Curvature of the Stomach

description: An area of hepatocytes that are closest to an arteriole. Because of their close proximity to oxygenated blood, the cells in this zone carry out oxidative processes such as beta-oxidation, cholesterol synthesis and gluconeogenesis.
label: Liver Acinus Zone 1

description: The lower part of the stomach that connects to the duodenum.
label: Pylorus

description: The proximal segment of the large intestine that is located in the right side of the abdominal cavity. It includes the cecum (with the attached appendix) and the ascending colon.
label: Right Colon

description: The portion of the colon that connects to the descending colon above and the rectum below.
label: Sigmoid Colon

description: The bend at the junction of the transverse and descending colon.
label: Splenic Flexure

description: The most distal section of the ileum that is continuous with the cecum.
label: Terminal Ileum

description: The surface of the tooth facing or in direct contact with the oral mucosa of the cheek.
label: Buccal Surface

description: Any one of the air-filled spaces within the ethmoid, frontal, maxillary, or sphenoid bones, which communicate with the nasal cavity.
label: Paranasal Sinus

description: A sinus of the meatuses of the nasal cavity.
label: Ethmoid Sinus

description: A pyramidal-shaped, thin-walled, air-filled cavity located in the maxilla. It is lined by mucus membrane and periosteum (mucoperiosteum) which contains cilia. It is adjacent to the nasal cavity and communicates with the middle meatus of the nose. It is the largest paranasal sinus and is composed of three recesses: alveolar, zygomatic, and infraorbital.
label: Maxillary Sinus

description: The arched strip of hair on the bony ridge above each eye socket.
label: Eyebrow

description: The posterior one third of the tongue behind the terminal sulcus that forms the anterior aspect of the oro-pharynx responsible for swallowing and modification of the voice in speech.
label: Base of Tongue

description: The part of the face below the lower lip and including the protruding part of the lower jaw.
label: Mentum

description: The horseshoe-shaped part of the oral cavity bounded superiorly by the ventral surface of the tongue, inferiorly by the mylohyoid muscle, anterolaterally by the gingival surfaces of the mandible, and posteriorly by the anterior tonsillar pillar.
label: Floor of Mouth

description: The bony anterior part of the roof of the mouth separating the nose from the mouth.
label: Hard Palate

description: The lower part of the pharynx that connects to the esophagus.
label: Hypopharynx

description: Paired, almond-shaped exocrine glands situated superior and posterior to each orbit of the eye that produce and secrete the watery serous component of tears.
label: Lacrimal Gland

description: The cartilaginous structure of the respiratory tract between the pharynx and the trachea. It contains elastic vocal cords required for sound production.
label: Larynx

description: Fleshy fold which surrounds the opening of the mouth.
label: Lip

description: The proximal portion of the respiratory passages on either side of the nasal septum lying between the floor of the cranium and the roof of the mouth and extending from the face to the pharynx. The nasal cavity is lined with ciliated mucosa, extending from the nares to the pharynx.
label: Nasal Cavity

description: The part of the pharynx in the back of the throat, at and above the soft palate. The nasopharynx is continuous with the nasal passages.
label: Nasopharynx

description: The part of the pharynx between the soft palate and the upper portion of the epiglottis.
label: Oropharynx

description: The roof of the oral cavity. It separates the oral cavity from the nasal cavity.
label: Palate

description: A hollow tube that starts posterior to the mouth and nasal cavity and ends superior to the trachea and esophagus.
label: Pharynx

description: A triangular-shaped area of mucosa located posterior the last mandibular molar tooth.
label: Retromolar Trigone

description: The area of the head comprised of the nasal cavity and paranasal sinuses.
label: Sinonasal Tract

description: The muscular extension of the hard palate which comprises the posterior of the oral cavity and the floor of the nasal cavity.
label: Soft Palate

description: The inferior portion of the urinary bladder which is formed as the walls of the bladder converge and become contiguous with the proximal urethra.
label: Bladder Neck

description: The funnel-shaped proximal portion of the ureter located within the kidney into which urine is secreted, from the collecting duct system of the kidney.
label: Renal Pelvis

description: The division of the urinary tract comprising the kidney and the ureters.
label: Upper Urinary System

description: The infratentorial compartment of the cranial cavity. Its boundaries are formed by the sphenoid bone, temporal bone, and parietal bone, and it contains the cerebellum and brain stem.
label: Posterior Cranial Fossa

description: The paired upper chambers of the heart. The left atrium receives oxygenated blood from the pulmonary vein and pumps blood into the left ventricle. The right atrium receives venous deoxygenated blood from the entire body via the superior and inferior vena cavae and pumps blood into the right ventricle.
label: Cardiac Atrium

description: A major abdominal artery that arises from the abdominal aorta below the diaphragm.  It supplies blood to the digestive organs. It has three major branches, left gastric artery, common hepatic artery, and splenic artery.
label: Celiac Artery

description: The portion of the abdominal aorta that lies below the kidneys.
label: Infrarenal Aortic Segment

description: A large vein which returns blood from the head, neck and extremities to the heart.
label: Vena Cava

description: The veins which return blood from the kidneys to the vena cava.
label: Renal Vein

description: The peritoneal reflection of the superior part of the posterior wall of the vagina, anterior to the rectum, which is the deepest point of the peritoneal cavity in females.
label: Recto-Vaginal Pouch

description: The portion of the lower extremity between the knee and the ankle. For clinical purposes this term is also used to refer to the whole inferior limb.
label: Leg

description: The portion of the lower extremity between the knee and the ankle on the left side of the body.
label: Left Leg

description: A part of the lower limb, located between hip and knee.
label: Thigh

description: A part of the lower limb, located between the hip and the knee and located on the left side of the body.
label: Left Thigh

description: A part of the lower limb, located between the hip and the knee and located on the right side of the body.
label: Right Thigh

description: The structure found below the ankle joint.
label: Foot

description: The portion of the upper extremity between the shoulder and the elbow. For clinical purposes this term is also used to refer to the whole superior limb.
label: Arm

description: The portion of the upper extremity between the shoulder and the wrist and located on the left side of the body.
label: Left Arm

description: The structure on the upper limb, between the elbow and the wrist.
label: Forearm

description: The distal portion of the upper extremity. It consists of the carpus, metacarpus, and digits.
label: Hand

description: A fold of peritoneum originating at the stomach and supporting the viscera.
label: Omentum

description: A large fold of peritoneum that hangs down from the stomach, and extends from the stomach to the posterior abdominal wall after associating with the transverse colon.
label: Greater Omentum

description: The bottom most subdivision of either the right or left lung.
label: Lower Lobe of the Lung

description: The larger lobe of the left lung, situated below and behind the oblique fissure.
label: Lower Lobe of the Left Lung

description: The lobe of the right lung situated below the oblique fissure.
label: Lower Lobe of the Right Lung

description: Either of the two (upper or lower) lobes that comprise the left lung.
label: Lobe of the Left Lung

description: The smaller lobe of the left lung, situated above and in front the oblique fissure, which includes the apex.
label: Upper Lobe of the Left Lung

description: The lobe of the right lung, situated above the horizontal fissure, which includes the apex.
label: Upper Lobe of the Right Lung

description: The smallest lobe of the right lung, situated above the oblique fissure and below the horizontal fissure.
label: Middle Lobe of the Right Lung

description: A part the bronchial tree of the right lung, an air passage arising from any segmental bronchus of the right lung and passing to the naturally delimited part of lung segment (subsegment), where it further subdivides into smaller passages.
label: Subsegmental Bronchus of Right Lung

description: A small tongue-like projection from the lower portion of the upper lobe of the left lung.
label: Lingula of the Lung

description: The layer of dense fibrous tissue that surrounds the splenic parenchyma.
label: Splenic Capsule

description: The tissues that surround the organs that are present within the abdominal cavity. The abdominal wall tissue is composed of layers of fat, parietal peritoneum, fascia, and muscles.
label: Abdominal Wall

description: The total system of structures outside the lungs that move as a part of breathing; it includes all structures from the skin to the parietal pleura.
label: Chest Wall

description: A portion of the peritoneal cavity formed by the greater and lesser omentum. It is located posteriorly to the stomach and extends into the greater omentum.
label: Omental Bursa
